HEADWORD: Phanerite
<hw>Phan"er*ite</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧n"⟦etil⟧r*⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>fanero`s</grk> visible, from <grk>fai`nein</grk> to bring
to light.]</ety> <def>Evident; visible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Phanerite series</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>the
uppermost part of the earth's crust, consisting of deposits produced by
causes in obvious operation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phanerocarpae</ent>⟦br⟧
